1.2 Data Architecture

1.2.1 Quantum Health Record (QHR) Database

```
Storage Architecture:
├─ Quantum Distributed Ledger:
│  ├─ Type: Permissioned quantum blockchain
│  ├─ Consensus: Quantum Byzantine agreement
│  ├─ Nodes: 1000+ healthcare providers globally
│  ├─ Block time: 1 second
│  ├─ Capacity: 10TB per block (for medical images)
│  └─ Security: Quantum digital signatures on every block

├─ Quantum Database Design:
│  ├─ Schema: 
│  │  ├─ Patients: Quantum identity + metadata
│  │  ├─ Encounters: Quantum-encrypted visit records
│  │  ├─ Diagnostics: Quantum AI analysis results
│  │  ├─ Treatments: Quantum-signed prescriptions
│  │  ├─ Genomics: Quantum-hashed genome data
│  │  ├─ Imaging: Quantum-compressed medical images
│  │  └─ Sensors: Real-time quantum sensor streams
│  ├─ Indexing: 
│  │  ├─ Quantum search indices (Grover algorithm)
│  │  ├─ Multi-dimensional quantum indexing
│  │  └─ Real-time update capability
│  └─ Query Processing:
    ├─ Quantum SQL extensions
    ├─ Natural language quantum queries
    ├─ Image similarity quantum search
    └─ Genomic pattern quantum matching

├─ Data Storage Tiers:
│  ├─ Tier 1: Hot storage (real-time access)
│  │  ├─ Technology: Quantum RAM (QRAM)
│  │  ├─ Capacity: 1PB per major hospital
│  │  ├─ Access time: <1μs
│  │  └─ Cost: $10/GB
│  ├─ Tier 2: Warm storage (frequent access)
│  │  ├─ Technology: Superconducting quantum memory
│  │  ├─ Capacity: 100PB globally distributed
│  │  ├─ Access time: <1ms
│  │  └─ Cost: $1/GB
│  └─ Tier 3: Cold storage (archive)
    ├─ Technology: Quantum error-corrected storage
    ├─ Capacity: 1EB (exabyte) globally
    ├─ Access time: <1s
    └─ Cost: $0.01/GB

└─ Data Processing Pipeline:
  ├─ Ingestion: 1PB/day global medical data
  ├─ Processing: Real-time quantum AI analysis
  ├─ Storage: Quantum-encrypted, distributed
  ├─ Access: Role-based quantum access control
  └─ Archival: Quantum compression then cold storage
```

1.2.2 Quantum Genomic Database

```
Sequencing Infrastructure:
├─ Quantum DNA Sequencers (1000+ units globally):
│  ├─ Technology: Quantum nanopore sequencing
│  ├─ Speed: Whole genome in 5 minutes
│  ├─ Accuracy: 99.9999% (Q50+ quality score)
│  ├─ Cost: $10 per genome (at scale)
│  └─ Output: 1TB raw data per genome (includes epigenetic)

├─ Processing Pipeline:
│  ├─ Step 1: Raw sequence to quantum bits
│  │  ├─ Conversion: ATCG → 00,01,10,11
│  │  ├─ Error correction: Quantum error correction codes
│  │  └─ Compression: Quantum compression to 1% size
│  ├─ Step 2: Variant calling
│  │  ├─ Algorithm: Quantum HMMs (Hidden Markov Models)
│  │  ├─ Speed: 1 million genomes/hour
│  │  └─ Accuracy: 99.99% for all variant types
│  ├─ Step 3: Annotation and interpretation
│  │  ├─ Quantum AI for functional prediction
│  │  ├─ Population frequency analysis
│  │  ├─ Clinical significance assessment
│  │  └─ Treatment implication mapping
│  └─ Step 4: Storage and indexing
    ├─ Storage: 100GB compressed per genome
    ├─ Index: Quantum search indices for all variants
    └─ Access: Quantum homomorphic encryption for privacy

├─ Global Genomic Database:
│  ├─ Target: 1 billion genomes by 2040
│  ├─ Storage: 100EB total (100GB × 1B)
│  ├─ Distributed: Across 100 data centers globally
│  ├─ Privacy: Quantum encryption, differential privacy
│  └─ Access: Federated quantum learning only

└─ Analysis Capabilities:
  ├─ Population genetics: Quantum PCA on 1B genomes
  ├─ Disease association: Quantum GWAS (genome-wide association)
  ├─ Pharmacogenomics: Quantum prediction of drug response
  ├─ Rare disease: Quantum matching across global database
  └─ Evolution tracking: Quantum analysis of pathogen evolution
```

