│  └─ Electrolytes: Na⁺, K⁺, Ca²⁺ at μM precision

└─ Position and Motion:
  ├─ Accelerometer: 0.001g precision, 3-axis
  ├─ Gyroscope: 0.01°/s precision
  ├─ Magnetometer: Earth's field tracking for orientation
  └─ Location: Quantum-enhanced dead reckoning

Processing Capabilities:
├─ On-chip Quantum Processor:
│  ├─ Type: Photonic quantum processor
│  ├─ Qubits: 10 physical qubits
│  ├─ Operations: 1000 quantum gates/second
│  ├─ Memory: 1kB quantum RAM
│  └─ Applications: Real-time anomaly detection, data compression

├─ Classical Processor:
│  ├─ Architecture: RISC-V with quantum extensions
│  ├─ Speed: 100MHz clock
│  ├─ Memory: 64kB SRAM, 1MB flash
│  └─ Power: 10μW active, 0.1μW sleep

└─ AI Capabilities:
  ├─ Edge AI model: Quantum neural network for anomaly detection
  ├─ Training: Federated quantum learning updates
  ├─ Inference: 100 inferences/second at 10μW
  └─ Personalization: Adapts to individual patterns

Communication:
├─ Quantum Body Area Network (QBAN):
│  ├─ Protocol: Quantum UWB (Ultra Wide Band)
│  ├─ Frequency: 3.1-10.6GHz
│  ├─ Data rate: 1Gbps
│  ├─ Range: 10m (to wearable hub)
│  ├─ Power: 1mW transmit, 0.1mW receive
│  └─ Security: QKD with wearable hub (new key every second)

├─ Direct Quantum 6G (Emergency mode):
│  ├─ For emergency beacon when hub unavailable
│  ├─ Data rate: 1Mbps
│  ├─ Range: Direct to satellite (with body penetration loss)
│  └─ Power: 10mW (short bursts)

└─ Inter-sensor communication:
  ├─ Mesh network between implants
  ├─ Synchronized measurements
  └─ Distributed computation

Manufacturing and Deployment:
├─ Fabrication: CMOS-compatible quantum dot process
├─ Yield: 90% at wafer scale
├─ Cost: $100 per unit at volume (1M+ units)
├─ Sterilization: Gamma radiation compatible
