```
Specialized for diabetes management:

Sensing Technology:
├─ Primary: Quantum fluorescence resonance energy transfer (FRET)
│  ├─ Glucose-binding protein labeled with quantum dots
│  ├─ Fluorescence changes with glucose concentration
│  ├─ Sensitivity: 0.1mg/dL
│  ├─ Response time: <1 second
│  └─ Lifetime: 1 year continuous operation

├─ Secondary: Quantum impedance spectroscopy
│  ├─ Measure tissue impedance at quantum frequencies
│  ├─ Correlates with glucose via hydration changes
│  └─ Provides redundancy and calibration

└─ Tertiary: Quantum Raman spectroscopy
  ├─ Direct molecular fingerprint of glucose
  ├─ Absolute measurement (no calibration needed)
  └─ Cross-validates other measurements

Features:
├─ Continuous monitoring: 1 measurement per second
├─ No fingerstick calibration needed
├─ Predictive hypoglycemia alerts (30 minute warning)
├─ Integration with insulin pumps
├─ Meal detection and carbohydrate counting
└─ Exercise adaptation

Size: 2×2×1mm (subcutaneous)
Power: 5μW average
Cost: $50 (disposable, 1-year lifespan)
```

