9.0 RISK MANAGEMENT AND MITIGATION

9.1 Technical Risks

```
Risk 1: Quantum Hardware Not Ready in Time
├─ Probability: 30%
├─ Impact: High (delays entire project)
├─ Mitigation:
│  ├─ Multiple technology approaches (superconducting, photonic, trapped ions)
│  ├─ Classical-quantum hybrid solutions as bridge
│  ├─ Investment in hardware development
│  └─ Phased deployment based on hardware readiness
└─ Contingency: Focus on classical AI with quantum enhancements

Risk 2: Integration with Existing Systems Fails
├─ Probability: 40%
├─ Impact: Medium (limits adoption)
├─ Mitigation:
│  ├─ API-first design from beginning
│  ├─ Legacy system integration modules
│  ├─ Pilot integrations early and often
│  └─ Standards development with existing vendors
└─ Contingency: Parallel systems during transition

Risk 3: Accuracy Below Clinical Requirements
├─ Probability: 20%
├─ Impact: High (cannot be deployed)
├─ Mitigation:
│  ├─ Extensive validation against gold standards
│  ├─ Conservative deployment (assistive not autonomous)
│  ├─ Continuous improvement through learning
│  └─ Human oversight requirements
└─ Contingency: Use as screening tool, not diagnostic

Risk 4: Scale Challenges
├─ Probability: 50%
├─ Impact: Medium (limits reach)
├─ Mitigation:
│  ├─ Design for scale from beginning
│  ├─ Modular architecture
│  ├─ Gradual scaling with learning
│  └─ Manufacturing partnerships
└─ Contingency: Focus on high-value applications first

Risk Budget: 30% of development budget ($150B in Phase 1)
```

9.2 Regulatory and Ethical Risks

```
Risk 1: Regulatory Approval Delays
├─ Probability: 60%
├─ Impact: High (delays deployment)
├─ Mitigation:
│  ├─ Early and continuous engagement with regulators
│  ├─ Design for regulatory compliance from start
│  ├─ Clinical trials designed for regulatory acceptance
│  ├─ International harmonization efforts
│  └─ Regulatory science development
└─ Contingency: Deploy in less regulated markets first

Risk 2: Privacy Concerns Limit Adoption
├─ Probability: 40%
├─ Impact: Medium (limits data sharing)
├─ Mitigation:
│  ├─ Privacy by design (quantum encryption, differential privacy)
│  ├─ Transparent privacy policies
│  ├─ Patient control of data
│  ├─ Strong security with independent audits
│  └─ Education about privacy protections
└─ Contingency: Local processing options

Risk 3: Ethical Concerns About Enhancement
├─ Probability: 30%
├─ Impact: Medium (limits certain applications)
├─ Mitigation:
│  ├─ Ethical frameworks developed with diverse input
│  ├─ Public dialogue and education
│  ├─ Gradual introduction with monitoring
│  ├─ Focus on therapeutic applications first
│  └─ International ethical standards
└─ Contingency: Opt-in for enhancement features

Risk 4: Liability and Malpractice Concerns
├─ Probability: 50%
├─ Impact: Medium (increases costs)
├─ Mitigation:
│  ├─ Clear liability frameworks
│  ├─ Insurance products developed
│  ├─ Human oversight requirements
│  ├─ Extensive testing and validation
│  └─ Transparency about limitations
└─ Contingency: Liability caps with insurance
```

